{
  "stem": "3012.5",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "However, we did not dare to move out from the camp, not even for a free walk around the perimeter, because we were still afraid of the SS and what happened.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Just a few days before liberation-- I believe it was before liberation-- the Russians were not in there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I don't remember they were in there yet.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A young woman was-- some-- one of the women was shot in the yard of the camp by the SS.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So the Russian army came and liberated the camp on the day of the Nazi surrender, which was on the 8th-- on the 8th of May, 1945.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We would have preferred the Americans, but you can't have the Americans all the time.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Sooner or later, we had to leave the camp, because the Russians-- I'm sure they meant well, but to this bunch of emaciated prisoners, who could barely walk, they gave one of those heavy Russian soups and they broke up the storage facilities of the camp and just everybody-- they let in everybody there.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And of course, people were grabbing whatever they could and started to eat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Everybody was starving.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The meagerest.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At the beginning, compared to Auschwitz, it was-- it was acceptable.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Acceptable-- it's-- you have to take it in terms of-- of acceptable food in a camp, not acceptable food in normal life.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that-- we-- we-- so one day, that the lower floor and the mezzanine.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Was filled ankle deep with human excrement.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, you opened the door, and you couldn't go in.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we knew at this moment, we had to-- we had to leave the camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So we went into one of the empty storage facilities.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
